review_content:
@aeysha.ferdous:The perfume bottle has changed more than 15 years.
The shape was like a drop.

V

@the reviewer below me: oh for fucks sake, don’t give perfume to a 3 year old. We get it, you don’t like it. For the kid’s sake, I hope you’re joking.

Anyway, I don’t love this but I also don’t hate it. It is very sweet and it doesn’t have much in the way of grounding notes. I thought marmalade was going to make for an interesting note, but this is a super sweet linear black currant perfume. If you’re in the camp that likes La Vie Est Belle and the like, you’ll probably like this.

It’s pretty fleeting. Longevity is like 2 hours before I am either anosmic or it has simply evaporated. Projection is close. That’s to be expected or something with such a small note pyramid, though.

